  "notes_content": "<h2>Ordination &amp; Clustering</h2><p>PCoA on Bray-Curtis distances projects sample-to-sample dissimilarity into 2D. Samples that cluster share community composition; axis percentages (when reported) tell you how much variance each component captures. Three or fewer percent on a primary axis usually means the structure isn't well-separated.</p><p>The two complex-heatmaps below show the same information from different angles: the taxonomy-clustered matrix highlights which taxa drive the sample groupings, while the symmetric Bray-Curtis matrix shows pairwise distances directly (dark = similar).</p>",
